But the terms were subsequently abused by heresy and invested with a technical heretical meaning3 and it then became necessary to restrict the Catholic phraseology to exactly defined expressions. Thus ἕνωσις καθ’ ὑπόστασιν, unitio, were the orthodox terms by which the Personal Union was expressed, and the heretical expressions were disclaimed: κρᾶσις as Apollinarian3 συναφεῖα, associ- atio, as Nestorian3 σύγχυσις, commixtio, as Eutychian.
